channel.title: What the %^!# is this?
channel.description:
Ok, Im getting pissed off, the most this week, my internet was FINE yesterday, now, it took about LITERALLY 10 Minutes to load up this page and none of the images work, it happens on all sites..
Even take a look at this.
[URL=http://www.speedtest.net][IMG]http://www.speedtest.net/result/145658195.png[/img][/URL]
Im seriously pissed, why the hell is my internet acting like this?

item.title: What the %^!# is this?
item.dc:creator: @daycrawler daycrawler
item.description:
@daycrawler wrote:

[quote=“The Un-Named, post:24, topic:116709”][quote author=daycrawler link=topic=165987.msg1547987#msg1547987 date=1182923124]

He posts with a serious question, and you guys see this as a chance to what, spam and show off your lifeline’s speed?
[me=The Un-Named]is not amused.[/me]

We didn’t post it to amuse you. You have the powers to clean it up if you wanted to so don’t complain because you can do something about it.
On Topic: You can call your ISP and ask if they are doing an install of servers, or if their was just a kink in the line etc. Just call them and explain your issue to them and they try to fix it. It could also be caused by your router and/or modem not functioning properly.
[/quote]

However, I shouldn’t need to clean everything up as soon as someone thinks it’s a good idea to show off, no offense or anything but these forums are really going downhill and I’m here to stop it.[/quote]
I don’t think they can go much further down.[br][size=1]Posted on: June 26, 2007, 07:06:56 PM[/size][hr][quote=“Casey., post:25, topic:116709”][quote author=The Un-Named link=topic=165987.msg1548014#msg1548014 date=1182923952]

However, I shouldn’t need to clean everything up as soon as someone thinks it’s a good idea to show off, no offense or anything but these forums are really going downhill and I’m here to stop it.
[/quote]
